                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/95: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-15T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 15, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Your 95, May 14, noon. The Department perceives no objection to the
                    publication by the Government of Honduras of the substance of its 40, May 13, 3
                    p.m. It is believed however that it would be desirable for you to examine the
                    text of the proposed statement prior to its publication.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
